text: The Canton Carnegie Library, at 225 E. 4th St. in Canton, South Dakota, was built in 1913. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 2016. It is a raised one-story building with basement built of brick with sandstone trim, upon a concrete foundation. With accompanying 11 photos from 2015 It was designed by Huron, South Dakota architect George Issenhuth. ==References== Category:Carnegie libraries in South Dakota Category:National Register of Historic Places in Lincoln County, South Dakota Category:Buildings and structures completed in 1913
